45:35.959 --> 45:37.583
I can't face Cami.

45:38.625 --> 45:40.000
They're better off without me.

45:43.458 --> 45:44.542
Drink your coffee.

45:44.542 --> 45:47.458
I just don't have it, man.

45:49.125 --> 45:50.750
I don't have the strength.

45:52.458 --> 45:55.250
Let me go. Just...

45:55.250 --> 45:56.125
...let me go.

46:02.625 --> 46:03.875
Look at me.

46:06.166 --> 46:07.750
You think you're
such a fuckup?

46:07.750 --> 46:09.333
You got everything, man.

46:09.333 --> 46:11.583
Everything that matters,
you've got.

46:11.583 --> 46:13.250
You think that was an accident?

46:13.250 --> 46:15.417
You built that family.

46:15.417 --> 46:17.917
Right? You built that business.

46:17.917 --> 46:20.667
Hard work.
Recovery every day.

46:20.667 --> 46:23.458
You have a life.
You have people that love you.

46:23.458 --> 46:24.875
'Cause you deserve it.

46:28.667 --> 46:31.542
So shut the hell up,
you whiny bitch.

46:31.542 --> 46:32.083
Drink your coffee.

46:37.375 --> 46:39.291
And then you're
gonna start over.

46:47.834 --> 46:51.041
I hurt my hand on your
fuckin' ribs.

46:51.041 --> 46:53.875
- Yeah. I think you might've
broke one, too.

46:53.875 --> 46:56.417
Good, asshole.
I owe you.

46:56.417 --> 46:57.667
[scoffs]

46:57.667 --> 46:59.375
[woman] Hey. Hey, turn that up.

46:59.375 --> 47:01.125
[newscaster]  And the search

47:01.125 --> 47:03.083
for the most hated man
in Chicago continues,

47:03.083 --> 47:04.625
as the fate of the Michael
Jordan statue's arm

47:04.625 --> 47:07.875
remains a mystery.

47:07.875 --> 47:10.834
Somebody cut off the arm
of the Michael Jordan statue?

47:11.917 --> 47:14.417
What kind of asshole would
do something like that?

47:18.875 --> 47:19.000
No.

47:20.500 --> 47:23.291
No way.

47:23.291 --> 47:24.959
It's just 'cause I--
I love him so much, man.

47:27.250 --> 47:29.291
What did I do with it?

47:29.291 --> 47:31.333
Because, you know...

47:31.333 --> 47:34.291
I-I'll be burned at the stake
if people find out.

47:34.291 --> 47:35.625
It's take care of.

47:36.667 --> 47:39.709
♪ driving rock music ♪

47:39.709 --> 47:44.875
♪♪♪

47:52.458 --> 47:55.041
[timer ticking]

47:58.458 --> 47:59.875
Lady?

48:00.375 --> 48:02.083
What?

48:04.208 --> 48:05.709
- Do you have any kids?
- No.

48:05.709 --> 48:07.041
You didn't want any?

48:10.542 --> 48:11.583
I can't.

48:14.166 --> 48:15.333
Sorry.

48:15.333 --> 48:17.417
Go to hell.

48:17.417 --> 48:19.208
There's a gay guy,
a black dude,

48:19.208 --> 48:21.500
and a terrorist with a baby
here to bail you out.

48:22.875 --> 48:24.041
[Mia] Let your baby live!

48:27.250 --> 48:28.709
- Hi, Franny!
- There's your mommy.

48:28.709 --> 48:29.750
Thank you.

48:34.041 --> 48:34.709
There you go.

48:34.709 --> 48:37.125
You're the best, Frank.

48:37.125 --> 48:39.792
And congratulations
on Employee of the Month.

48:39.792 --> 48:42.375
Can't imagine why
it took so long.

48:42.375 --> 48:43.792
[both laugh]

48:43.792 --> 48:45.458
Frank Gallagher?

48:45.458 --> 48:46.667
Chuck Hartley.

48:46.667 --> 48:47.667
From corporate.

48:47.667 --> 48:49.208
Oh!

48:49.208 --> 48:51.250
A pleasure to meet
one of the elite.

48:51.250 --> 48:52.917
Can we talk for a minute
in Mr. Singh's office?

48:52.917 --> 48:54.500
Sure.

48:54.500 --> 48:55.417
[man over PA]
Go to the loading dock.

48:55.834 --> 48:57.792
Go to the loading dock, please.

49:00.125 --> 49:01.750
Adeeb's not joining us?

49:01.750 --> 49:03.583
I'm-I'm sorry to say no.

49:03.583 --> 49:06.792
Um... [sighs]

49:06.792 --> 49:10.500
Mr. Singh was
let go yesterday.

49:10.500 --> 49:11.542
[sighs]

49:12.750 --> 49:15.583
Chuck, if I may,
this is not easy for me.

49:15.583 --> 49:19.125
Adeeb was a dear friend
as well as a colleague.

49:19.125 --> 49:20.750
He took a chance on me.

49:20.750 --> 49:22.875
In a way, he gave me
a new life.

49:22.875 --> 49:24.208
He was first-rate, all right.

49:24.208 --> 49:27.500
So you can understand that...

49:27.500 --> 49:29.875
...though I am flattered...

49:29.875 --> 49:32.542
...and yes, ready to step
into his place,

49:32.542 --> 49:34.834
I do it with a heavy heart.

49:34.834 --> 49:38.250
I'd thought it would be
a while before I replaced him.

49:38.250 --> 49:40.166
Oh. [chuckles]

49:40.166 --> 49:40.792
Frank...

49:40.792 --> 49:43.333
you have the wrong idea.

49:44.333 --> 49:46.166
Oh.

49:46.166 --> 49:47.333
Is that so?

49:47.333 --> 49:49.792
Well, if this is a, uh...

49:49.792 --> 49:52.208
a move to corporate...

49:52.208 --> 49:54.542
I'm here to let you go, too.

49:54.542 --> 49:55.875
What?

49:58.792 --> 49:59.792
Today is your last day.

49:59.792 --> 50:02.458
I-I don't understand.

50:02.458 --> 50:05.000
I'm Employee of the Month.
What did I do wrong?

50:05.000 --> 50:07.208
Oh, my gosh. Nothing.

50:07.667 --> 50:10.125
Nothing at all.

50:10.125 --> 50:12.458
You were the model employee.

50:14.625 --> 50:18.000
Corporate is shutting down
the store.

50:18.000 --> 50:21.208
Half the stores
in the country, actually.

50:22.583 --> 50:24.166
See, the Internet gutted us,

50:24.166 --> 50:28.750
like a--an alien popping out
of our stomachs

50:28.750 --> 50:30.542
and eating our brains.

50:33.959 --> 50:36.000
I'm working my way
across the country

50:36.000 --> 50:37.542
like the Angel of Death.

50:39.875 --> 50:42.875
And once I finish
burying Spokane,

50:42.875 --> 50:45.041
there'll only be one man
left to fire.

50:45.041 --> 50:46.166
Who's that?

50:46.500 --> 50:48.625
Myself.

50:56.125 --> 50:58.000
I wish you luck, my friend.

50:58.834 --> 51:00.792
Thank you, Chuck.

51:00.792 --> 51:03.834
But men like us--
we land on our feet.

51:03.834 --> 51:05.959
We're diligent,
dependable, honest.

51:05.959 --> 51:09.792
We got gumption,
can-do spirit.

51:09.792 --> 51:11.792
Temporary setback at best.

51:12.542 --> 51:14.166
Right.

51:23.041 --> 51:24.250
[timer ticking]

51:26.583 --> 51:29.250
Dang it!
Ah, we're running out of time!

51:29.250 --> 51:30.291
I got this.

51:32.208 --> 51:34.083
[Davey] I'll get the pills.

51:34.083 --> 51:34.917
Allah 'akbar!

51:34.917 --> 51:37.834
[overlapping shouting]

51:37.834 --> 51:38.750
[woman] Seriously?!

51:38.750 --> 51:40.583
Allah 'akbar!

51:40.583 --> 51:42.750
Allah!

51:42.750 --> 51:44.917
[overlapping screams]

51:44.917 --> 51:47.166
[man] Come on, let's go!

51:47.166 --> 51:49.834
Can I have the morning after
pill, please?

51:49.834 --> 51:52.875
♪ upbeat music ♪

51:52.875 --> 51:58.000
♪♪♪

52:20.792 --> 52:23.000
What do you think?

52:26.083 --> 52:27.959
[whispering] What do you think?

52:27.959 --> 52:29.542
[laughs] Oh!

52:29.542 --> 52:31.625
Not a chance, pal.

52:31.625 --> 52:36.291
♪♪♪

52:36.291 --> 52:37.291
[chuckles]

52:37.291 --> 52:41.458
♪♪♪

53:07.333 --> 53:08.458
[crying]

53:13.834 --> 53:15.875
♪ laid-back rock music ♪

53:15.875 --> 53:20.500
♪♪♪

53:20.500 --> 53:24.166
Ladies and gentlemen, do you
believe in miracles?

53:24.166 --> 53:26.333
Because the city of Chicago
woke to find

53:26.333 --> 53:27.834
the lost dunking arm
of Michael Jordan

53:27.834 --> 53:30.333
has reappeared,

53:30.333 --> 53:31.500
now planted at Ping Tom Park--

53:31.500 --> 53:34.000
or as the citizens of Chicago
are demanding,

53:34.000 --> 53:36.208
"His Airness Memorial Park."

53:36.208 --> 53:39.959
MJ's arm reaches majestically

53:39.959 --> 53:42.375
and eternally to the heavens.

53:42.375 --> 53:44.667
What could be more fitting?

53:44.667 --> 53:45.750
John, back to you.

53:45.750 --> 53:51.667
♪♪♪
